Rating: 2
This one's a bit of a mixed bag. I don't think it was awful at all, like some of the other reviewrs, but it definitely isn't amazing either. It took a bit of tweaking to get it to something we enjoyed. I used wholewheat fusilli as that's what we keep in the cupboard and most of the ingredients were on hand already in the kitchen, with was a big plus. I did use some tomato paste to help 'saucify' the pasta and a little fresh parmesan at the end helped, though I don't think it was necessary. All in all, I wouldn't go out of my way to cook it, but I do think it's a great recipe for a quick and easy dinner or for a pasta salad to take to work.

